{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"83c16df6-b1bb-4640-ab01-804b96ab50b1","content":"Use the `--filter` option with `FullyQualifiedName` or `ClassName`:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nor\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator means \"contains\", so the first form matches any test whose fully qualified name includes `ReportExporterTests`. The second form matches the exact class name.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"258d25eb-0bea-4bbc-98e1-ef56a2f169f8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only a specific test class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the `dotnet test` CLI filter syntax.","outputTokens":167,"requestId":"340A:3A1698:AB804B:C9501A:69F4019F"},"id":"e61602d8-ba52-44b5-abec-0b1ed3592355","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:28:02.831Z","parentId":"5824f0a8-2a3d-4fcf-8efc-c9b763e4d393"}
